HEADWORD: Filipino
<hw>Filipino</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>of or relating to the
Philippines or its people or customs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Philippine.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>of or relating to the language of the
Philippines.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Tagalog.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filipino</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Filipino
<hw>Fil`i*pi"no</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu>pl.
<plw>Filipinos</plw> <pr>(#)</pr></plu>. <ety>[Sp.]</ety> <def>A native
or inhabitant of the Philippine Islands, specif. one of Spanish descent
or of mixed blood.</def> <wns>[wns=1]</wns></p>

<p><q>Then there are <qex>Filipinos</qex>, -- ⟦ldquo⟧children of the
country,⟦rdquo⟧ they are called, -- who are supposed to be pure-blooded
descendants of Spanish settlers. But there are few of them without some
touch of Chinese or native blood.</q> <rj><qau>The
Century.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>the official language of the Philippines, based on
Tagalog. It draws its lexicon from other Philippine languages.</def>
<wns>[wns=2]</wns>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Philippine.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

